<note xml:id="ch36n100"><p id="ch36n100pa1">An imperfect, but original, picture of Gaul, more especially of Auvergne, is shewn by Sidonius; who, as a senator, and afterwards as a bishop, was deeply interested in the fate of his country. See l. v. [<hi rend="italic">leg.</hi> vii.] epist. i. 5, 9, &amp;c.</p></note>

