<note xml:id="ch36n105"><p id="ch36n105pa1">When the Capitol ceased to be a temple, it was appropriated to the use of the civil magistrate; and it is still the residence of the Roman senator. The jewellers, &amp;c., might be allowed to expose their precious wares in the porticoes.</p></note>

