<note xml:id="ch36n129"><p id="ch36n129pa1">Theophanes, who calls him a Goth, affirms that he was educated, nursed (), in Italy (p. 102); and, as this strong expression will not bear a literal interpretation, it must be explained by long service in the Imperial guards.</p></note>

